&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.rwth-aachen.de/cms/root/Studium/Lehre/Exzellente-Lehre/~dhky/Dean-s-List/?lidx=1&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;RWTH Aachen University&amp;rsquo;s Dean&amp;rsquo;s List&lt;/a&gt;. For my master thesis under supervision from 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://thisisalex.de/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Alexander von Rohr&lt;/a&gt; and 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.dsme.rwth-aachen.de/cms/DSME/Das-Institut/Team/~jlolt/Prof-Sebastian-Trimpe/?allou=1&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Sebastian Trimpe&lt;/a&gt; on parameter search in time-varying environments using Bayesian optimization I received the 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.sew-eurodrive-stiftung.de/en/#student-award&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;SEW-EURODRIVE Student Award&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My current research evolves around uncertainty quanitifaction when learning system dynamics and detecting changes in system dynamics with probabilistic quarantees. Furthermore, I am interested in Bayesian optimization&amp;ndash;specifically in high-dimensional and time-varying approaches.&lt;/p&gt;
